cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.MM, cs.HC, cs.AI 

The paper deals with facial micro-expression recognition using deep neural networks, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG). The use of optical flow features also suggests a possible fit with multimedia (cs.MM) and human-computer interaction (cs.HC) sub-categories. Additionally, the use of complex objective functions and feature extraction techniques aligns with the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category.
